Node.Notes: Uncertain. Could refer to city of Shechem or common noun shoulder/ridge, the latter of which could be taken to refer to either Mount Gerizim (near Shechem) or just a portion of land in general.
Uncertain. Some argue that the common noun shechem, shoulder/ridge, is feminine and so the masculine numeral one has to be to refer to Joseph: as one above your brothers.
Could be delayed relative clause to shechem/portion or assumes: [It is that] which I took ...
